President Obama announced his intent to nominate several individuals to key Administration posts. These include David S. Adams for Assistant Secretary for Legislative Affairs at the Department of State, Luis A. Aguilar for Commissioner at the Securities and Exchange Commission, Marcos Edward Galindo for Member of the Board of Trustees of the Barry Goldwater Scholarship and Excellence in Education Foundation, John A. Heffern for Ambassador to the Republic of Armenia, Harry Hoglander for Member of the National Mediation Board, Gregory Karawan for Member of the Board of Directors of the Securities Industry Investor Corporation, Patricia M. Loui for Member of the Export-Import Bank of the United States, Maria E. Ruess for Member of the Board of Trustees of the Barry Goldwater Scholarship and Excellence in Education Foundation, and Susan L. Ziadeh for Ambassador to the State of Qatar. President Obama expressed confidence in the capabilities of these individuals and looks forward to working with them in the future. The article provides brief biographical information about each nominee.